otland national football team|Scotland]]\n|align=left|1 October 1985\n|align=left|30 June 1986\n{{WDL|10|3|4|3|decimals=1}}\n|<ref>{{cite web |title=History archives: Managers: Alex Ferguson |url=http://www.scottishfa.co.uk/football_manager_profile.cfm?page=3087&managerID=11 |publisher=Scottish Football Association |accessdate=30 March 2017 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170330083910/http://www.scottishfa.co.uk/football_manager_profile.cfm?page=3087&managerID=11 |archive-date=30 March 2017 |url-status=dead  }}</ref>\n|-\n|align=left|[[Manchester United F.C.|Manchester United]]\n|align=left|6 November 1986\n|align=left|19 May 2013\n{{WDL|1500|895|338|267|decimals=1}}\n|<ref>{{cite web |title=Managers: Alex Ferguson |url=http://www.soccerbase.com/managers/manager.sd?manager_id=48 |work=Soccerbase |publisher=Centurycomm |accessdate=30 March 2017}}</ref>\n|-\n!colspan=3|Total\n{{WDLtot|2155|1253|490|412|decimals=1}}\n!\u2014\n|}\n\n==Published works==\n* {{cite book | last1 = Ferguson | first1 = Alex | last2 = Meek | first2 = David | title = Alex Ferguson: 6 Years at United | publisher = Mainstream | location = | year = 1992 | isbn = 978-1851584444 }}\n* {{cite book | last1 = Ferguson | first1 = Alex | last2 = Fitton | first2 = Peter | title = Just Champion!| publisher = [[Manchester United Football Club]] | location = | year = 1993 | isbn = 978-0952050919}}\n* {{cite book | last1 = Ferguson | first1 = Alex | last2 = Ball | first2 = Peter | title = A Year in the Life: The Manager's Diary | publisher = [[Manchester United Football Club]] | location = | year = 1995 | isbn = 978-1852275211}}\n* {{cite book | last1 = Ferguson | first1 = Alex | last2 = Meek | first2 = David | title = A Will to Win: The Manager's Diary | publisher = Andre Deutsch | location = | year = 1997 | isbn = 978-0233993683}}\n* {{cite book | last = Ferguson | first = Alex | title = The Unique Treble | publisher = Hodder & Stoughton | location = | year = 2000 | isbn = 978-0340792612}}\n* {{c