{"title_page": "List of people with an anxiety disorder", "text_new": "{{short description|Wikipedia list article}}\nNumerous notable people have had some form of [[anxiety disorder]]. This is a list of people accompanied by verifiable source associating them with one or more anxiety-based mental health disorders based on their own public statements; this discussion is sometimes tied to the larger topic of [[creativity and mental illness]]. In the case of dead people only, individuals with a [[Retrospective diagnosis|speculative or retrospective]] diagnosis should only be listed if they are accompanied by a source reflective of the mainstream, academic view. Individuals should not be added to this list unless the disorder is regularly and commonly mentioned in mainstream, reliable sources.\n\n== List ==\n__NOTOC__{{compact ToC|side=yes|top=yes|num=no}}\n\n[[File:Leonardo DiCaprio visited Goddard Saturday to discuss Earth science with Piers Sellers (26105091624) cropped.jpg|thumb|right|150px|American actor [[Leonardo DiCaprio]]]]\n[[File:Shawn Mendes Live in Concert (cropped).jpg|thumb|right|150px|[[Shawn Mendes]] chronicled his experiences in the song \"[[In My Blood (Shawn Mendes song)|In My Blood]]\"]]\n[[File:WinonaRyderSept08.jpg|thumb|right|150px|American actress [[Winona Ryder]]]]\n[[File:Sarah Silverman, 2012.jpg|thumb|right|150px|American comedian [[Sarah Silverman]]]]\n\n== A ==\n*[[Adele]], Grammy-winning British singer who suffered from anxiety and panic attacks<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.dailystar.co.uk/showbiz/497525/Adele-therapist-tour-help-combat-anxiety-fear-flying-stage-fright|title=Adele takes therapist on tour to help her combat anxiety|date=28 February 2016|publisher=}}</ref>\n*[[Jessica Alba]], American actress who struggled with [[obsessive\u2013compulsive disorder]]<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.depression-guide.com/celebrities/jessica-alba.htm|title=Jessica Alba|website=www.depression-guide.com}}</ref>\n*[[Woody Allen]], American film director who struggled with obsessive-compulsive disorder<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.femalefirst.co.uk/celebrity/Woody+Allen-3295.html|title=Woody Allen is an obsessive compulsive|website=Female First}}</ref>\n\n== B ==\n*[[Cardi B]], American rapper<ref name=independent>{{cite web|first=Sabrina|last=Barr|date=6 February 2019|title=Cardi B and Missy Elliott help to destigmatise anxiety with candid Twitter exchange|work=[[The Independent]]|url=https://www.independent.co.uk/life-style/health-and-families/cardi-b-missy-elliott-anxiety-mental-health-twitter-sarah-silverman-a8765521.html}}</ref>\n*[[Kim Basinger]], American actress who suffered from social anxiety<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.beyondanxietyanddepression.com/celebrities-anxiety/kim-basingers-battle-social-anxiety|title=Kim Basinger's Battle With Social Anxiety|website=Beyond Anxiety and Depression|date=January 23, 2013|author=Gloria Goodwin}}</ref>\n*[[David Beckham]], English footballer who struggled with obsessive-compulsive disorder<ref>{{cite web|author=Maxine Frith|url=https://www.independent.co.uk/news/uk/this-britain/beckham-reveals-his-battle-with-obsessive-disorder-6104728.html|title=Beckham reveals his battle with obsessive disorder|date=3 April 2006|publisher=[[The Independent]]}}</ref>\n*[[Justin Bieber]], Canadian singer who struggled with depression and anxiety<ref>{{cite web |last1=Abrams |first1=Margaret |title=Justin Bieber reveals struggles with anxiety and opens up about his marriage in new Seasons documentary trailer |url=https://www.standard.co.uk/insider/alist/justin-bieber-reveals-struggles-with-anxiety-and-opens-up-about-his-marriage-in-new-seasons-a4346121.html |publisher=Evening Standard |date=27 January 2020}}</ref>\n*[[Kristen Bell]], American actress who struggles with anxiety<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=mYUQ_nlZgWE |accessdate=January 29, 2018|title=Kristen Bell Explains There Is No Shame In Feeling Anxiety & Depression|author=The Off Camera Show with